It's be thankful.

20:59.136 --> 20:59.777
And I try.

20:59.797 --> 21:02.780
I am nothing without Him.

21:05.482 --> 21:08.185
It is He that is everything within me.

21:10.788 --> 21:13.790
I don't deserve any earthly thing that God has blessed me with.

21:14.851 --> 21:20.557
But I'm thankful that God loves me enough to bless me that way anyway.

21:22.939 --> 21:25.682
Listen, church, and I mean just with every fiber in me,

21:26.210 --> 21:30.434
I don't ever want to be part of the other nine.

21:32.716 --> 21:34.278
I don't ever want to be found that way.

21:36.861 --> 21:40.184
I want my Lord and savior to always find me thankful.

21:41.445 --> 21:45.929
I want him to always find me grateful and faithful.

21:47.431 --> 21:54.578
In this passage of scripture, I use it again and again, but it drops a heavy burden on me for those who are.

21:55.394 --> 21:56.235
the other nine.

21:58.718 --> 22:00.961
It burdens me for the church at large.

22:02.643 --> 22:09.431
I believe that we need to ask the question this way, is the North American church part of the other nine?

22:11.834 --> 22:13.536
Is that the state of the church today?

22:14.397 --> 22:21.746
Are we the ones who God has blessed over and over again, but don't stop long enough to turn around and say, thank you, Jesus.

22:24.258 --> 22:34.152
Are we the ones that go through these religious motions like Leviticus describes to us like these nine did when they went to the priest to show their healing?

22:34.172 --> 22:44.867
Are we the ones who go through the motions of reading our Bibles and praying and showing up sometimes at church but not living thankfully or any differently as a result of those things?

22:47.811 --> 22:52.498
Listen, church, have we come to Jesus?

22:53.730 --> 22:59.098
like this Samaritan foreigner and had an encounter with Jesus.

23:00.741 --> 23:01.462
Have we had that?

23:02.223 --> 23:05.729
Have we seen His grace at work in our lives?

23:09.375 --> 23:16.626
If we have, then listen, it's time that we are overwhelmingly thankful for that.

23:17.986 --> 23:19.290
The church at large.

23:19.311 --> 23:25.050
It's time that we stop playing around with religion and get serious about Jesus and sharing His Word.

23:25.973 --> 23:27.378
Our world is lost.

23:28.578 --> 23:31.501
We need to share the Word of God with everyone we see.

23:31.961 --> 23:35.964
It's time that we can become a people of thanksgiving, a people of gratitude.

23:36.265 --> 23:39.808
It's time we become a people of love and of grace and of forgiveness.

23:40.108 --> 23:45.713
It's time that we become a people who sacrifice our time and our talents and service to the Lord and to others.

23:46.053 --> 23:51.858
It's time that we get involved in all of our local churches helping to build God's kingdom as we're called to do so.

23:51.918 --> 23:53.360
Listen, folks, this is important.

23:53.760 --> 23:58.564
It's time that the church stops following the nine and begins to follow Jesus.

23:58.544 --> 24:01.968
That's where we are.

24:03.689 --> 24:16.483
In my prayer for you today, for everyone in this room, everyone who's going to be listening on Facebook, wherever you are, that we are part of the one, not part of the nine.

24:17.764 --> 24:21.428
We should be praising Jesus like this Samaritan man, amen?

24:22.769 --> 24:23.730
Yes, we should.

24:24.418 --> 24:25.339
Yes, we should.

24:25.399 --> 24:28.343
We should follow on our face at the feet of the mighty God.

24:28.643 --> 24:35.832
He's done great things for all of us if we will just stop for one second and take notice as to what Jesus does for us.

24:37.695 --> 24:38.676
We must do this.

24:39.317 --> 24:40.378
We should be thankful.

24:41.339 --> 24:49.810
Every step we take, we should be more and more thankful as we show what God has done for us in our lives.

24:51.392 --> 24:52.914
We should recognize that God

24:53.410 --> 24:54.672
Showers us daily.

24:55.693 --> 24:57.816
Do you know you were showered every day with blessings?

25:00.739 --> 25:03.122
Don't miss these chances to live a thankful life.

25:04.564 --> 25:08.870
I'll give you another scripture in that book of James chapter 1 verse 17 tells us this.

25:10.932 --> 25:14.016
Every good, perfect gift is from where?

25:15.558 --> 25:17.140
Yeah.

25:17.160 --> 25:21.906
Comes down from the father of the heavenly lights who doesn't change like shifting shadows.

25:22.562 --> 25:24.725
in the good that we serve and unchanging God.

25:27.128 --> 25:28.851
We get so much to be thankful for.

25:30.613 --> 25:43.191
Our God Church, listen, through this Thanksgiving, and from now on, remember, our God is worthy of our praise every day.

25:43.251 --> 25:51.282
When we really stop to remind ourselves how God gives us, we should be overwhelmed

25:52.002 --> 25:56.629
with the desire to praise the Creator who has given us everything.

25:59.033 --> 26:01.457
My prayer this morning is that you recognize Jesus.

26:03.300 --> 26:09.810
You're living thankful for all that He does in your lives, every headbound, every eye closed.

